General.Name: TPG Telecom Ltd
General.Description: TPG Telecom Limited provides telecommunications services to consumer, business, enterprise, and government and wholesale customers in Australia. The company owns and operates fixed and mobile network infrastructure, including fixed voice and data network with approximately 28,000 kilometers of metropolitan and inter-capital fiber networks; and 7,000 submarine cable systems. It also offers enterprise ethernet, cloud, SD-WAN, mobility, internet of things, and answering and messaging services. It provides its services under the Vodafone, TPG, iiNet, AAPT, Internode, Lebara, and felix brands. The company was formerly known as Vodafone Hutchison Australia Limited and changed its name to TPG Telecom Limited in June 2020.TPG Telecom Limited was founded in 1986 and is based in Barangaroo, Australia.
